Following the court ruling on Monday which ordered that the Convener of the #revolutionNow protest, Mr Sowore Omoyele,and his co-defendant, Mr Olawale Bakare to be remanded in the custody of the Department of State Services, Soworo lamented that “This is a lawless country.” Sowore, stated this in an interview with pressmen on his way out of court after being ordered to remain in the DSS while condemning his detention. Read also: https://dailytimes.ng/court-remands-sowore-co-defendant-in-dss-custody/ However,Sowore was cut short by security operatives who pulled him out of the court premises. Read also: https://dailytimes.ng/sowore-dss-involved-in-physical-fight-in-court/ While he was struggling with the security agents,Sowore began to recite solidarity songs to his supporters. Sowore was arraigned along with his co-defendant, Mr Olawale Bakare, by the Federal Government on seven charges lingering on conspiracy to commit treasonable felony and money laundering among others. They, however, pleaded not guilty to the charges against them. Again, Justice Ijeoma Ojukwu fixed Friday for the hearing of their bail application.